2026-06-24 00:34:50,710 DEBUG msg #13: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01UiacwaA2kMxW1tvCwMFw2F): {"assignees":[{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTUyOTQ4","login":"SilvioBaratto","name":"Silvio Angelo Baratto Roldan","databaseId":0}],"body":"## Goal\nThe heart of Cycle 3: a `FeatureBuilder` that **consumes** a martj42 results frame plus a pre-computed `EloResult` and `TeamAbilities` and emits one frozen feature-row value object per match plus a tidy DataFrame. Here Elo (consumed), Dixon-Coles attack/defence (consumed), confederation/ranking (issue #7), and the time-aware form/rest/goal-diff helpers (issue #8) compose into the final **football-only** covariate vector for historical training matches. Elo and Dixon-Coles are passed in (DI) and **never recomputed** here.\n\n## Context\nThis is `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`, the module named in the cycle objective. Verified contracts the builder consumes:\n- `compute_elo(df, EloConfig) -> EloResult`. `EloResult.match_diffs: list[MatchEloDiff]` is **1:1 with the engine's internally-sorted rows** (same sort reproduced by `sort_chronological` in issue #8). `MatchEloDiff` fields: `date, home_team, away_team, home_elo, away_elo, elo_diff, neutral` — `home_elo`/`away_elo`/`elo_diff` are already **pre-match** and `elo_diff` is **venue-agnostic** (excludes home advantage). Pull these directly; do not recompute.\n- `fit_dixon_coles(df, PoissonConfig) -> TeamAbilities` with `.attack: dict[str,float]`, `.defence: dict[str,float]`, `home_adv`, `rho`, `intercept`. A single **global** fit → a lookup table keyed by canonical team name. Attack is mean-zero-normalized, so a missing team → neutral `0.0`.\n- Input frame schema from `Martj42Loader.load_results()`: `DATE` (object ISO), `HOME_TEAM`/`AWAY_TEAM` (normalized), `HOME_GOALS`/`AWAY_GOALS` (nullable `Int64`, `<NA>` unplayed), `TOURNAMENT`, `NEUTRAL` (bool).\n- Issue #7 supplies `resolve_ranking` / `confederation_of` / `CONFEDERATIONS` and `FeatureBuildConfig`. Issue #8 supplies `sort_chronological`, `recent_form`, `rest_days`, `goal_difference`.\n\n**No-leakage join (the load-bearing invariant):** `sorted_df = sort_chronological(df)` is byte-identical to the Elo engine sort, so `elo.match_diffs[i]` aligns positionally with `sorted_df.iloc[i]`. Add a **per-row alignment guard** asserting `(diff.home_team, diff.away_team, diff.date) == (row.HOME_TEAM, row.AWAY_TEAM, row.DATE)` and raise a clear `ValueError` on drift rather than silently emit leaked features. All time-aware helpers are called with `before_idx=i` so a match never sees its own or later results.\n\n**Scope guard:** consume Elo/Poisson — do NOT recompute or refit them in `build()`. No model training / `[rf]` (Cycle 4), no Monte Carlo/backtest (Cycle 5). **Football-only:** no socio-economic/market-value/GDP/odds columns ever appear in the output.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Output frame has exactly one row per input match (including unplayed WC2026 rows) with a stable, documented column set; labels (`home_goals`/`away_goals`) pass through as `<NA>` for unplayed.\n- [ ] **Football-only allow-list test:** the exact output column set is asserted — no GDP/market-value/odds fields present.\n- [ ] `elo_diff == home_elo - away_elo` for every row (consumed, not recomputed); attack/defence columns equal the values in a hand-built `TeamAbilities` passed in (proves no refit).\n- [ ] Neutral flag round-trips exactly from the input `NEUTRAL` column.\n- [ ] A constructed two-match history shows match-2 features using only match-1 information (end-to-end no-leakage test).\n- [ ] Misaligned Elo/df input raises `ValueError` (alignment-guard test).\n- [ ] Confederation columns are deterministically encoded over the six `CONFEDERATIONS` indicators; a `None` ranking degrades to confederation without breaking the frame.\n- [ ] Deterministic given `FeatureBuildConfig.random_seed`.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #7: feat: static confederation map + FIFA-ranking fallback resolver + [features_build] config\n- #8: feat: time-aware recent-form, rest-days, and goal-difference helpers\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`\n  - Frozen dataclass `MatchFeatures` (the `FittedDistribution`/`MatchEloDiff`-style record): `date, home_team, away_team, neutral, home_elo, away_elo, elo_diff, home_attack, home_defence, away_attack, away_defence, home_form, away_form, home_rest_days: float | None, away_rest_days: float | None, home_goal_diff, away_goal_diff, home_confederation: str | None, away_confederation: str | None, home_ranking: float | None, away_ranking: float | None, home_goals: int | None, away_goals: int | None`. As a pure data record it may exceed the 50-line class budget (same exemption as `MatchEloDiff`).\n  - `FeatureBuilder(config: FeatureBuildConfig, *, ranking=None, confed_map=CONFEDERATION_MAP)` with `build(df, elo, abilities) -> list[MatchFeatures]` and `build_frame(df, elo, abilities) -> pd.DataFrame`. Keep methods < 10 lines by delegating to the issue-#7/#8 helpers.\n  - `to_frame(rows: list[MatchFeatures]) -> pd.DataFrame` — tidy output; deterministic one-hot of the two confederation columns into the six indicators (fixed column order).\n  - Module-level factory `build_features(df, config=None, *, ranking=None) -> pd.DataFrame` — convenience that calls `compute_elo` + `fit_dixon_coles` once when the caller does not supply them; the primary `build()` accepts pre-computed `EloResult`/`TeamAbilities` (DI, no recompute when shared across historical + WC2026 frames).\n- **Modify:** none (exports wired by the final exports task).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_features_build.py` — BDD naming; in-memory martj42-shaped frames; pass a hand-built `TeamAbilities` and a real `compute_elo` result; assert the allow-list, alignment guard (`ValueError`), no-leakage, neutral round-trip, determinism. No network/I/O.\n- Conventions: `from __future__ import annotations`; module-level pure helpers above the class; `|` unions; `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFhg","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"FF0000"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-pro","color":"7057FF"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACoqMq5A","name":"area:features","description":"Area: features","color":"0052CC"}],"milestone":{"number":3,"title":"Cycle 3 — Football-Only Covariates","description":"Build per-match feature vectors: Elo, Elo-difference, FIFA ranking (confederation as fallback), time-weighted recent form, goal difference, Dixon-Coles attack/defence abilities, rest days, confederation, neutral-venue flag. All football-only (no socio-economic/market-value). Assemble from martj42 (historical) + live WC2026 adapter (current state).","dueOn":null},"state":"OPEN","title":"feat: core per-match feature assembler over martj42 history (features/build.py)"}
