Done. Here's what was implemented:

**`worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`** (new, ~190 lines):
- `MatchFeatures` — frozen dataclass with 23 fields covering all football-only covariates
- `_TeamState` — O(N) incremental rolling state per team (deque of last `window` played results, last match date). Eliminates the O(N²) prefix scans of the raw `timeaware` helpers
- `FeatureBuilder(config, *, ranking, confed_map).build(df, elo_df, abilities, *, ranking_df=None) → pd.DataFrame` — sorts chronologically, validates alignment, assembles features in one pass
- `FEATURE_COLUMNS` — documented stable tuple used by the allow-list test
- Re-exports `TeamAbilities` so consumers can `from worldcup_playoff.features.build import TeamAbilities`

**Key guarantees satisfied:**
| Criterion | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| One row per match, unplayed → NA | builder never drops rows; `_na_to_none()` + `Int64` dtype |
| `elo_diff == home_elo − away_elo` | computed directly from consumed `elo_df` |
| Abilities consumed, not refit | `ab.attack.get(home, 0.0)` — no fitting call anywhere |
